<p />
<h1><a name="Installation_Procedure"></a> Installation Procedure </h1>
<p />
on    
<p />
on    
<p />
<p />
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Install_the_rsv_gwms_tester_pack"></a> Install the rsv-gwms-tester packages </span></h2>
<p />
The RPM is available in the OSG repository:
<p />
Install the RPM and dependencies (be prepared for a lot of dependencies).
<p />
   <pre class="rootscreen">[root@client ~]$ yum install rsv-gwms-tester</pre>
  <pre class="rootscreen">[root@client ~]$ yum install glideinwms-userschedd</pre>
<p />
This will install the current production release verified and tested by OSG with default condor configuration.
<p />
If you wish to install a different version of GlideinWMS, add the "--enablerepo" argument to the command as follows:
<p /> <ul>
<li> <code>yum install --enablerepo=osg-testing rsv-gwms-tester</code>: The most recent production release, still in testing phase.  This will usually match the current tarball version on the GlideinWMS home page.  (The osg-release production version may lag behind the tarball release by a few weeks as it is verified and packaged by OSG).  Note that this will also take the osg-testing versions of all dependencies as well.
</li></ul> 
<p />
<p />
<p />
<h2 class="twikinetRoundedAttachments"><span class="twikinetHeader"><a name="Configuration"></a> Configuration </span></h2>
<p /> <ol>
<li> Modify the file <pre>/etc/rsv/metrics/org.osg.local-gfactory-site-querying-local.conf</pre> to adjust the constraints for the entries that you are interested in testing
</li> <li> Add your central manager DN to the authorization list. <pre class="rootscreen">[root@client ~]$glidecondor_addDN -allow-others -daemon 'Central Manager DN' '/the/central/manager/DN' condor </pre>
</li> <li> Copy the schedd config files to the condor-cron dir  <pre class="rootscreen">[root@client ~]$ cp /etc/condor/config.d/* /etc/condor-cron/config.d/</pre>
</li> <li> Add file  <pre>/etc/condor-cron/config.d/98&#95;public&#95;interface.config</pre> with the following contents: <pre>NETWORK&#95;INTERFACE &#61; REPLACE&#95;ME&#95;WITH&#95;HOST&#95;IP</pre>
</li> <li> Start <pre>httpd, condor-cron, rsv</pre> services. 
</li> <li> Run <pre> rsv-control --enable  org.osg.local-gfactory-site-querying-local --host fermicloud053.fnal.gov </pre> where host can be localhost or the actual name of the node where rsv-vo-gwms is installed.
</li> <li> Run <pre>rsv-control --on  org.osg.local-gfactory-site-querying-local  --host fermicloud053.fnal.gov </pre> where host can be localhost or the actual name of the node where rsv-gwms-tester is installed
</li></ol> 
<p />
<p />
